HEADWORD: Flytting
<hw>Flytt"ing</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Contention; strife; scolding; specif., a kind of
metrical contest between two persons, popular in Scotland in the 16th
century.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark></p>

<p><q>These ⟦ldquo⟧<qex>flytings</qex>⟦rdquo⟧ consisted of alternate
torrents of sheer Billingsgate poured upon each other by the
combatants.</q> <rj><qau>Saintsbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flittingly</ent>⟦br⟧
